This paper discusses the initialization of weights in neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on the variance of preactivation and its preservation across layers. This topic is closely related to deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that deals with deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
